GENERAL TECHNIQUES:
- Show don't tell - Use action and dialogue over exposition
- Vary sentence structure - Mix short and long for rhythm
- Use specific details - Concrete imagery over abstractions
- Stay in scene - Avoid summary or time skips within scene
- Start in media res - Begin with action or dialogue, not setup
- Metaphor restraint - Maximum 1-2 per scene, save for key moments
- POV discipline - One perspective per scene, no exceptions
- Description economy - 30% description, 70% action/dialogue
- Every word counts - If it doesn't advance plot or reveal character, cut it